<br>
Destruction:<br>
Very easy trial.  Bring at least 3 classes that can tank.  (time geared necroes offtank very well here BTW)  Bard sings ae slow along with normal songs.  Getting things slowed is less important than getting them debuffed so your casters can do DPS.  Mob DPS is so weak that as long as healers arent getting interrupted or you have horribly undergeared people you will be fine. Just kill 20 things under the time limit, then the FULLY slowable boss.  (my group has easily broken 30 things dead)<br>
<br>
Efficiency:  AKA the caster belt trial.  (MMM clickie belt drops here)  Each wave spawns 3-4 mobs, Elites and commanders are slightly harder than the soldiers.  The soldiers hit amazingly weak.  Think PoV mob DPS.  Stuff is mezzable here. but has insanely high MR.  it's better to pump DS and just tank everything.  There is an AE that reduces your HP and mana pool, play group DA song before you say &quot;begin&quot; and you avoid the first AE.  After that have all radiant cure classes cast it immeadiatly after the AE.  (Having warrior click epic about 10 seconds into wave 2 can be nice because some people will bounce the second AE.  You cannot DA through the 2nd-4th Aes because they come mid-wave.)  The boss is total chump.<br>
<br>
Ingenuity-  All this trial takes is a bard and a pet class.  Group sets up on on of the platforms with a dragorn weilding 2 visible weapons. Bard Spawns the boss and FM until you lose aggro.  group farms 2 bane weapons for the pet, and waits for repop (5 second repop) and farms a weapon for the tank.  Tank engages boss with 200+ damage sheild.  DS+ pet dmg = dead boss in a few minutes.  Only unresistables like harmtouch, mana/lifeburn can dmg boss.  By far the easiest trial with bard+mage.  For a real challenge try to beat it with more than 10 minutes remaining on the timer (you'll want 2 mages)<br>
<br>
Subversion (chests/lull trial)  Group parks on back wall except for chest disarmers.  you need 1 luller (bard best but clr/enc works) 1 bard/rog disarmer, 1 int caster, and 1 priest (or necro can disarm priest traps for some odd reason).  start trial and 6 chests pop of random type.  1 minute later roamers come from the zone-in.  2 up maximum at once.  Use PoP lull!! (SSoQ)  OOw lull does not work.  I've never had a lull resist, cirtical or non aggro. make sure chanters and clerics know this too.  Loot 300 points and roamers despawn, boss and 2 guards become targetable.  Lull the 2 guards and pull boss.  This boss is by far the most badass.  I have had a 14k hp well sheilded/AAd warrior die here more than once with a GoD geared 800+ AA'd cleric healing.  (only ghetto bard slow however).  I might add: subversion is the closest trial to zone, pretty quick to get to.<br>
<br>
Weaponry:  This trial is retarded.  all that truly matters is your weapon selection.  There should be an NPC outside that hands out loot when you hand him a blunt/slash and piercing weapon with a good ratio.  It's kinda dumb, but unless you have 2 rangers with full complements of Qvic + weapons you are going to fail this trial without a primo group.  A guildmate lead of group of (all time/&lt;Qvic geared) ranger, cleric, paladin, necro, enchanter, rogue, and didnt even make it past the second mob (of 4) before they timed out.  My regular group, however, has a 100% sucessrate. (very similair AA level, not positive on their weapon arsenals) We go in with rogue (all mobs take full dmg from backstabs, rogues MUST swap in piercers) ranger (uber slashing weapons, kinda gimpy piercing and blunt) warrior (uses that VDD clone from efficiency + riposte disc vs the blunt guy to do 10-15% damage in 12 seconds) bard (me using Q hammer/despair, songblade/EoE, and 2 velium gemmed pokers) necro (parses 750+ DPS versus Steelshock the low HP mob that only spells can hurt), and a cleric for heals, and pet/reverse DS/nukes on steelshock.  As a bard you swap weapons as required, keep haste/atk up at all times and don't slow in order to maximize dmg taken from DS.  There is no boss here.  But there is a quad-hitting 2300 named for war epic 2.0 enroute to weaponry trial. (Possesed Brute)<br>
<br>
Fear - By far the best trial.  Requires group make-up, gear, AAs, skill, and adaptation.  You must kill a certain number of things before time expires, and you must survive.  I've never not killed enough.  If you fail here it will be because you wiped.  There are 4 things around the outside (undead, dragorn, elemental, and wolf)  They summon a minion every few minutes (it's on a timer from when the last minion of that type died.)  If it's a light blue con minion it is fearable, but quads for 1300 with very high atk.  They also have very high magic resist, and must be malo'd or tashed for fear to be reliable.  These light blue cons have many hps (100K plus I think).  However Every tick they are feared a massive dot afflicts them draining about 15% of their health.  Fear is the only way to kill them.  Bard AE fear works well for keeping the 1300 hitters off your cleric or necro/chanter who is fearing.  However, bard fear may overwrite fear from others, I'm not sure, be carefull.  The minions also can summon dark blue mobs (it seems to be about 50/50, I've seen 4 drk blue at once and 4 light blue.  I've seen the first 6-8 all unfearable, that sucked.)  The dark blues hit 850ish and must be tanked/DPSd.  For this trial you absolutely need a debuffer and a dedicated fearer.  chanter, necro and cleric are best at fearing, however most clerics I know have never used fear or done any type of CC and make poor choices as primary fear class.  Necroes tend to have extended affliction items which make their fears last longer.  Bards are not as usefull here as in the other trials.  There is no boss.  Just kill stuff and survive. <p>-steps 70 bard of karana</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mearisthecowslayer>Mearis The Cowslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 229<br> <font color=#330000>(12/10